title: Glen Beicker Ranch Airport
text:
Glen Beicker Ranch Airport is a privately owned, public use <a href="airport">airport</a> located 10 <a href="nautical%20mile">nautical mile</a>s (19 <a href="kilometre">km</a>) east of the <a href="central%20business%20district">central business district</a> of <a href="Seguin%2C%20Texas">Seguin</a>, a city in <a href="Guadalupe%20County%2C%20Texas">Guadalupe County, Texas</a>, United States.
Facilities.
Glen Beicker Ranch Airport covers an area of 160 <a href="acre">acre</a>s (65 <a href="hectare">ha</a>) at an <a href="elevation">elevation</a> of 465 feet (142 m) above <a href="mean%20sea%20level">mean sea level</a>. It has one <a href="runway">runway</a> designated 17/35 with a <a href="grass">turf</a> surface measuring 1,950 by 50 feet (594 × 15 m).
